[{"id":"bcb04c98353fa6da9d6ba17eade48577","from":"J. Epstein","from_email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to":"LVJET@aol.com","to_list":[{"name":"LVJET@aol.com","email":"LVJET@aol.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Re: Gulfstream seat photos","date":"2007-07-10T01:55:35.000Z","formatted_date":"Jul 10, 2007","formatted_time":"1:55 AM","body":"definetely\n\n\n----- Original Message ----\nFrom: \"LVJET@aol.com\" <LVJET@aol.com>\nTo: JEEPROJECT@YAHOO.COM\nCc: JETCARE@aol.com; kellens@earthlink.net; gmax1@ellmax.com\nSent: Monday, July 9, 2007 7:15:48 PM\nSubject: Gulfstream seat photos\n\n\nJeffrey,\nI think we need to change the seat belt color to match the light leather, \nyour thoughts?\n \nsee attach photos\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSee what's free at AOL.com. \nLarry,\n            Attached are a few photos of 1 of the single seats nearing completion. Notice the seat belt webbing color. We did not change that. It is the same that was there with the other leather. Please ask J.E. if he wants to keep it that way.\n \n \nSincerely,\n \nJay Massar\nOperations Manager\n \n\n \nInternational Jet Interiors\n960 South Second Street\nRonkonkoma, NY 11779\n631.737.5900   Phone\n631.897.0974   Cell\n631.737.1249   Fax\n \njmassar@intljet.com   e-mail\nwww.intljet.com         website","body_html":"<html><head><style type=\"text/css\"><!-- DIV {margin:0px;} --></style></head><body><div style=\"font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt\"><DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">definetely<BR><BR>\n<DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">----- Original Message ----<BR>From: \"LVJET@aol.com\" &lt;LVJET@aol.com&gt;<BR>To: JEEPROJECT@YAHOO.COM<BR>Cc: JETCARE@aol.com; kellens@earthlink.net; gmax1@ellmax.com<BR>Sent: Monday, July 9, 2007 7:15:48 PM<BR>Subject: Gulfstream seat photos<BR><BR>\n<DIV><STRONG>Jeffrey,</STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>I think we need to change the seat belt color to match t